  meanings
    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "Abbreviation of million."
        entry
          definition Thousand
      partOfSpeech noun
    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "A prescribed quantity or extent."
        entry
          definition "The act or result of measuring."
        entry
          definition "Metrical rhythm."
        entry
          definition "A course of action."
      partOfSpeech noun
      synonyms (bar metric)
    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "(always meter) A device that measures things."
        entry
          definition "(always meter) A parking meter or similar device for collecting payment."
        entry
          definition "(always meter) One who metes or measures."
          example "a labouring coal-meter"
        entry
          definition "(elsewhere metre) The base unit of length in the International System of Units (SI), conceived of as 1/10000000 of the distance from the North Pole to the Equator, and now defined as the distance light will travel in a vacuum in 1/299792458 second."
        entry
          definition "(elsewhere metre) An increment of music; the overall rhythm; particularly, the number of beats in a measure."
        entry
          definition "(elsewhere metre) The rhythm pattern in a poem."
        entry
          definition "(elsewhere metre) A line above or below a hanging net, to which the net is attached in order to strengthen it."
        entry
          definition "A poem."
      partOfSpeech noun
    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "The international mile: a unit of length precisely equal to 1.609344 kilometers established by treaty among Anglophone nations in 1959, divided into 5,280 feet or 1,760 yards."
        entry
          definition "Any of several customary units of length derived from the 1593 English statute mile of 8 furlongs, equivalent to 5,280 feet or 1,760 yards of various precise values."
        entry
          definition "Any of many customary units of length derived from the Roman mile (mille passus) of 8 stades or 5,000 Roman feet."
        entry
          definition "The Scandinavian mile: a unit of length precisely equal to 10 kilometers defined in 1889."
        entry
          definition "Any of many customary units of length from other measurement systems of roughly similar values, as the Chinese (里) or Arabic mile (al-mīl)."
        entry
          definition "(travel) An airline mile in a frequent flier program."
        entry
          definition "Any similarly large distance."
          example "The shot missed by a mile."
        entry
          definition "A race of 1 mile's length; a race of around 1 mile's length (usually 1500 or 1600 meters)"
          example "The runners competed in the mile."
        entry
          definition "One mile per hour, as a measure of speed."
          example "five miles over the speed limit"
      partOfSpeech noun
    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "A half note, drawn as a semibreve with a stem."
        entry
          definition "A unit of volume, in the Imperial and U.S. customary systems, 1/60 fluid drachm. Approximately equal to 1 drop, 62 μL or 0.9 grain (weight) of water."
        entry
          definition "A short vertical stroke used in handwriting."
        entry
          definition "Anything very minute; applied to animalcula and the like."
          example "the minims of existence"
        entry
          definition "The smallest kind of worker in a leaf-cutter ant colony."
        entry
          definition "A little man or being; a dwarf."
        entry
          definition "A small fish; a minnow."
        entry
          definition "A short poetical encomium."
      partOfSpeech noun
    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "A unit of time equal to sixty seconds (one-sixtieth of an hour)."
          example "You have twenty minutes to complete the test."
        entry
          definition "A short but unspecified time period."
          example "Wait a minute, I’m not ready yet!"
          synonyms (instant jiffy mo moment sec second tic)
        entry
          definition "A unit of angle equal to one-sixtieth of a degree."
          example "We need to be sure these maps are accurate to within one minute of arc."
          synonyms ("minute of arc")
        entry
          definition "(chiefly in the plural, minutes) A (usually formal) written record of a meeting or a part of a meeting."
          example "Let’s look at the minutes of last week’s meeting."
        entry
          definition "A unit of purchase on a telephone or other network, especially a cell phone network, roughly equivalent in gross form to sixty seconds' use of the network."
          example "If you buy this phone, you’ll get 100 free minutes."
        entry
          definition "A point in time; a moment."
        entry
          definition "A nautical or a geographic mile."
        entry
          definition "An old coin, a half farthing."
        entry
          definition "A very small part of anything, or anything very small; a jot; a whit."
        entry
          definition "A fixed part of a module."
        entry
          definition "A while or a long unspecified period of time"
          example "Oh, I ain't heard that song in a minute!"
      partOfSpeech noun
      synonyms (instant jiffy mo moment sec second tic "minute of arc")
    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "A period into which a year is divided, historically based on the phases of the moon."
          example "July is my favourite month."
        entry
          definition "A period of 30 days, 31 days, or some alternation thereof."
          example "We went on holiday for two months."
        entry
          definition "(in the plural) A woman's period; menstrual discharge."
      partOfSpeech noun
  phonetic "/ɛmz/"
